    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="182"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/1047½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                        Counselor for the Department of State</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Polk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">28 January, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Counselor</hi>: Thank you for the
                        enclosed.<note n="36" xml:id="d182fn1">See <hi rend="italic"
                        >supra</hi>.</note> I dare say that for the present we may let this matter
                    stand as it does; but I hope that we shall soon have new material for judgment
                    in the shape of further information from our Ambassador at Tokyo. I do not think
                    that it will be safe or wise to leave the Japanese government in any doubt as to
                    the impression such an attitude on their part makes on us.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
